<div class="privacy-container">
    <div class="header">
        <h1>Privacy Policy – EduVision</h1>
    </div>

    <div class="privacy-content">
        At EduVision, your privacy is a top priority. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, store, and protect your data when you interact with our platform. By using EduVision, you agree to the practices outlined below.

        <p>1- Data Collection: We collect personal information such as your name, email address, and meeting activity to improve user experience and support platform functionality.</p>

        <p>2-AI Analysis Data: Our platform analyzes emotional and engagement data through camera and microphone inputs to assess student focus and comprehension. This data is used solely for educational purposes and is not shared without consent.</p>

        <p>3-Usage Logs: We log user activity such as meeting attendance, time spent in sessions, and performance metrics to help instructors track progress.</p>

        <p>4-Security Measures: We implement industry-standard encryption and data protection practices to keep your personal and session data safe.</p>

        <p>5-Data Sharing: Your data will never be sold. We may share anonymized data with educational partners to improve teaching strategies.</p>

        <p>6-Student Consent: Before joining any monitored meeting, students are informed about AI analysis and are required to provide consent.</p>

        <p>7-Third-party Services: EduVision may integrate with external services (e.g., video conferencing APIs). These services may collect data under their own privacy policies.</p>

        <p>8-Data Storage Duration: Collected data is retained only as long as necessary for educational purposes, after which it is securely deleted.</p>

        <p>9-User Control: Users can view, edit, or delete their personal information at any time via their profile settings.</p>

        <p>10-Cookies: We use cookies to enhance platform performance. You can choose to disable cookies via your browser, but some features may not work correctly.</p>

        <p>11-Policy Updates: EduVision may update this Privacy Policy. Users will be notified of significant changes via email or app notifications.</p>

        <p>12-Contact Us: For questions regarding your data or this policy, you can reach our Data Privacy Officer at privacy@eduvision.ai.</p>

        <strong>Your trust is important to us. EduVision is committed to maintaining transparency and safeguarding your digital learning journey.</strong>
    </div>
</div>
